str2: When, at which time. From hos and te; at which too, i.e. When.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To draw up, as a net to shore. From ana and a derivative of the base of basis; to cause to go up, i.e. Haul.
Sea-coast, (sandy) beach; shore (of sea or lake), land. From aisso and hals (on which the waves dash).

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: Another form for kathezomai; to seat down, i.e. Set; intransitively, to sit; figuratively, to settle.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To collect, gather. From sun and lego in its original sense; to collect.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Properly, beautiful, but chiefly good, i.e. Valuable or virtuous.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
A vessel, flask. From aggos; a receptacle.
A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I cast, throw, rush, (b) often, in the weaker sense: I place, put, drop. A primary verb; to throw.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Rotten, useless, corrupt, depraved. From sepo; rotten, i.e. Worthless.
Without, outside. Adverb from ek; out(-side, of doors), literally or figuratively.
